<zk>
	<label multiline="true"><![CDATA[
	ZK-6056: How to reproduce
	1. Click the chosenbox below to open the dropdown.
	2. Type "US" into the input field.

	Expected (with the fix): locales whose toString contains "US" appear,
	e.g. en_US, es_US, fr_US.

	Without the fix: nothing matches — the ListSubModel's default
	STRING_COMPARATOR filters by startsWith on the server, and no
	Locale.toString() starts with "US".

	The "contains" semantics is requested with the existing
	org.zkoss.zul.chosenbox.filterLogic attribute (here at component scope
	via custom-attributes; page / desktop / library scopes work the same
	way). When filterLogic="contains", the SubModel's startsWith pre-filter
	is bypassed so the chosenbox-level contains filter runs.
	]]></label>
	<zscript><![CDATA[
        ListModelList model = new ListModelList(Locale.getAvailableLocales());
        ListSubModel subModel = ListModels.toListSubModel(model);
    ]]></zscript>
    <chosenbox width="400px" model="${subModel}">
        <custom-attributes org.zkoss.zul.chosenbox.filterLogic="contains"/>
    </chosenbox>
</zk>
